<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title>Bonnie v<%=Bonnie::Version.current()%></title>
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", :media => "all" %>
    <%= render 'layouts/shim' %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="landing-masthead">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <h1 class="logo">BONNIE</h1>
            <p class="tagline">A tool for testing electronic clinical quality measures</p>
          </div>
          <div class="login col-md-4">
            <a href="/users/sign_in" class="btn-login">login</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="landing-subhead">
      <div class="container">
        <a target="_blank" href="/resource/Bonnie_user_guide.pdf" class="btn btn-default">learn more</a>
      </div>
    </div> 
    <div class="container">
      <section class="highlights row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>streamlined and efficient</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-fighter-jet lg"></i>
          <p>pretesting for eCQMs</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>developer empowerment</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-bolt lg"></i>
          <p>provides specific feedback on the behavior of the CQM logic</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>meaningful use support</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-plus lg"></i>
          <p>supports the Meaningful Use (MU) Program</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p class="lead">Bonnie is a tool for testing electronic clinical quality measures (eCQMs) designed to support streamlined and efficient pre-testing of eCQMs, particularly those used in the Meaningful Use (MU) program.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 section-heading">
          <h1 class="section-heading">Current <span class="version-num">Version 1.2</span></h1>
          <p>The version 1.2 release of Bonnie introduces a new compact visualization of the measure logic.  This compact visualization provides a high-level view of the measure logic, including a summary analysis of the structure of the logic. This provides a clear view into how a patient calculates against a measure and the level of test case coverage for sections of the logic. Additionally, this release resolves issues identified with SimpleXML and HQMF R2 measure import providing a more robust measure-loading infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h1 class="section-heading">Capabilities<span class="version-num"> v1.2</span></h1>
          <ul class="list-cap">
            <li>A compact visualization of measure logic
              <ul>
                <li>Allows a summary analysis of the measure structure</li>
                <li>Provides a compact view of test coverage</li>
                <li>Introduces a high level display of a synthetic test patient calculation against measure logic</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Improved measure import infrastructure for:
              <ul>
                <li>Measure Authoring Tool (MAT) SimpleXML</li>
                <li>HQMF R2.1</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <p>BONNIE is sponsored by the <a href="http://cms.hhs.gov/">Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS)</a> and <a href="http://healthit.gov">Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology (ONC)</a> and has been developed by <a href="http://www.mitre.org">The MITRE Corporation</a></p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>